heir adaptability in the twentieth century, while Michael Robinson adds an overview of modern Korean perceptions of Confucianism.Originally published in 1990.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPhilosophy, ConfucianxEast Asia. 0aPhilosophy, ConfucianzEast Asia. 7aRELIGION / Confucianism.2bisacsh1 aCollcutt, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbrey, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaboush, Jahyun Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobinson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRozman, Gilbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRozman, Gilbert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1980-1999z978311041344108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Religionz978311041357108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140086193440uhttps://www.de